 interfered. Very quiet man my dad was. And I used to say to myself - I used to feel sad for him sometimes, think - po old dad. Ain't you got anybody dad? He said, yes, one day, I have got a mother but - she's away, in a home somewhere, she's in a home. A
n
d I said, we won't mum - don't - don't go and see her? Oh very very rare, he said, but she very old, she don't know nobody, he said. And I thought then what a terrible time, when I - think of today how these people - go away and nobody goes near 'em well,
 that comes back sometimes see. They're very expensive ain't they? To buy. Mm.
