he said, I can't sit down. He said, my bottom's sore. And my mother just looked at \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 she said, well you'll never steal nothing else. But my mother said to her afterwards, there was no need to go any further, you hit him, that was quite enough - wi
thout going to the school. But she said, that's - she said to me and my sister, that's a little of what I'll do to you if I ever find that you ever touch anybody else's money what you shouldn't do, what is not yours is not yours, you always remember it. I
t
's funny you know. But she's dead nuts on anything like that. She'd kill you if you - you know, if you took - and my eldest sister went out once and - and - and - step cleaning one Saturday, we used to go step cleaning, that was another job - when she was
 
hard up you know, up In Iverdale Road, Nunhead, and my sister put a sixpence in her shoe and - she nearly kill - blooming killed her. 'Cos she went - pinched a sixpence, she - you know, she shoved it in her shoe, she said, I'll give you do me, she said, y
o
u're another one I'll stop it. And by God she did too, she - I don't know. She was a mother out of a thousand really you know. But mind you if you was in trouble she - she'd help you, you know, my sisters had their bad times you know and their husbands be
e
n out of work, they'd go to her, she'd help 'em. She'd help anybody, I give her her due there. She was good mother you know really in her way. But she used to say to me, you're the sauciest one of the lot. You've got more go - guts than any of them she sa
id, in my family she said the way you go on. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How old were you when you did step cleaning?
