ake it over night and do it in a steamer in the morning. Sort of thing, and boiled puddings we used to have. Boiled - she'd make boiled pudding with jam on and treacle like that what we had after dinner if we wanted it. And Sundays there was always a suet
 
pudding - in a roll, she'd always make a pudding in a roll, and cut it in pieces like that when you had your dinner, and - a big aitch bone of beef or a big - shoulder of lamb or - a lump of lovely beef you know, when you - when you think of them days wha
t you think - what you want today, my God. And no irons, no electric irons.
