 then she'd go round and see if it was all done, if not God be - then woe betide you if it wasn't done properly you had to do it again-, and we - in the front of our house we had a board - don't see them today - like just an ordinary board you stood over,
 that used to have to be as white as snow, because you could eat off of that board, because if you didn't she'd go - bloody made. She'd make you do it about three times 'til it come up white any rate.
