h where we went to always gave hot cross buns, and my mother - I used to say, oh I - I - I can't stop, I can't do so and so, not - I've got to get to the church this morning 'cos the hot cross buns, and she used to say, well your dad always brings home - 
m
y dad always brought the hot cross buns home, a couple of big bags of buns for us all you know, but that was the - that one - I got of the church was better than what that - what my dad brought home, to me it was, I had to be at church before anybody else
 to - climb up to get our hot cross bun. Oh it was a laugh. Oh yes, it was real funny.
