p the top end of this great big yard we had but - you wasn't able 'cos she - once you let the chickens out they - used to go and peck'em all the damn things, you know what chickens are and - all the ground and everything else so you couldn't have much - v
egetables or anything there. But she didn't mind, my mother didn't mind, long as she had all her - things round her, all her blooming - we used to have goldfish and ducks and - rabbits and - oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever collect anything like stamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I can't remember - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever go for long walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh yes, we did - go to the park every - if we had holiday my mum used to pack us up a great big sandwich - you know, sandwiches, and we'd have to go to Pepys Hill to the park there and she 
used to let us go there. But long as we was home by a certain time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What about bicycling, did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No bicycles, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Would you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 I remember my - she's asking my brother once
 to take me up Peckham Rye - it was on school holidays it was and he took me up Peckham Rye. And - he asked me to get on his back and he was going to give me - what they call it, flying chair or something - and - we was near - he was fishing. I'm - and I 
w
ent right over and in the pond. Oh, I wasn't very old, about six or seven, and - and oh dear, and he was worried about my mum you know what she'd say, she'd go off the deep end, so anyhow, I - he put me coat on, a good job me coat was dry, and he took, me
 home and she - she gave him a whack, gave me a smacked arse and all and sent me to bed, said, you should know better, she said, and as for you, you don't go out with her - fancy, wonder she don't get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457 pneumonia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 . Oh she was funny. But he was - that was the t
ime he - I believe he done it for the purpose 'cos he didn't want me to go, I mean, it's only nat - natural, boys want to go with the boys, they don't want to take the girls out but - she said, you take her up the park today and you play with her up there
.
 'Course he wanted to do the fishing and I - I didn't want him to fish so - he said all right then, he said, you get on my shoulders and hold me round the neck, and he said, I'll do me fishing. Of course I - and I went just over the top and went in. Oh de
a
r. We had about as far as the walk home from about - here to Sloane Square station, so you can guess I was in a sore plight by the time I got there. Oh she went up - stone mad. Oh honestly. Said, get to bed. So - I got a smacked behind, I remember getting
 
that, and she walloped him, and she said, as for you, letting her fall in the water, that's for you, you're old enough to know better, to get on his shoulders. But - if she could clout you my mum would do it you know, and used to hurt you. Nobody those da
y
s - no sauce - I was a saucy bugger you see and - and - I - I done any cheeking she's got me here to - and - from wall to the other I didn't know where it come from. Oh dear. But I - I suppose she thought it was all for me own good you know. But there you
 are, it's funny how your life how it is.
