ent there for about a week, and when I saw they pickled pickles and how they did 'em, I've never ate a pickle since. Even now I'm married, been married, I've been married fifty years come - come Christmas, Boxing Day, and I never - I but the pickles, they
 can all have 'em, but you wouldn't catch me eating any of 'em.
