Oh used to have to - push 'em down in the jars you know. And we - if you see - if you're doing stuffed olives, you have to get 'em all a cer
tain way. Heinz do a lot more stuff, but they only done pickles them days. Pickled gherkins and - pickled - stuffed olives and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was this after you got married or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Before I got married. And - oh yes, I've had a go at everything don't worry. I expect it was a bit more money, that's why I - went there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How much did you get in the tea packing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh - I can't remember now, it wasn't a great lot. Not - I wouldn't have much left with my mother took her share. 'Cos she always sort of took her share. And - you know, you was never allowed to have days off with her or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you have a half day with this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Only just the Saturday off you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You went from there to the pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Pickle factory Mm. Onl
y stopped a fortnight up there. I didn't like the smell of it either. I said to my mum - she said, well, you get another job. And then my brother came along and so I went into the picture palace you see. I was nearly twenty when I went in the picture pala
ce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What kind of hours did you work - there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Ay? Half past one - 'til about four o'clock. Well they never opened 'til two them days, and - I think they showed a film to about - and then we used to all continue all the time, but we used to - make 
our tea like - between us, the girls. I used to sometimes go about quarter to four 'til quarter to five and - and relieve them in the cash box and all that sort of thing. Used to be about three of us did the circle, and the men, they used to have the men 
a
t the bottom in the stalls part, and men in the gallery, no women, only I went - I didn't go there like that, I went in the - in the gallery bar and I used to sell ices and things like that. And it's a rough hole up the top and he said to me, the manager,
 
would I like to - go and work in the circle and I said I would, it's a bit rough up here. As I said - told my mum, I'd go home one day with me head under me arm, and he laughed, and of course he brought me - my mother used to buy my clothes right to when 
I got older, and - of course I went in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457  what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
name and then after I did the circle one of the girls left in the cash box and I went to - work in the cash box you know. It's been interesting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You enjoyed those jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you have holidays with pay in those jobs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, no, if you had your holiday you had to pay for it. Didn't have many holidays away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How many days a week would you work in the picture palace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh - six days. But they us
ed to give you a half a day in the week like - that was like - any day - from - from the time you used to start, 'til - you know, late at night because if you didn't - if you're in the cash box you'd have to work 'til nine, at least, but - in the circle, 
i
f you worked in the circle you was allowed to leave about half past eight. You see, don't never used to get many people in after about half past - if it - but if it was a Wednesday it was quite - sort of quiet day you know. No, I always remember the - nev
er done much on a Wednesday then like what they do today. That's why I think me and my old man can reckon up so well, 'cos we've had such a lot of money pass through our hands you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you think that the money you got in these jobs was a fair wage for those days or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Well - from - what I reckon it was - with the what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2642704\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
name you know them days. I mean it - nobody earnt a lot of money, not them days for any of their jobs really. Wasn't a lot of money about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you get on all right with your employers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh yes, yes. I've always been a person to get on. Even in the hospital, I was away for all that time, I - always got on with everybody you know. I do, I - well - it's not much use being otherwise - unless if I'm - if I'm put out I'm
 put out I'll tell you. Very bad tempered but - as I say, I don't have much it's pretty good really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever have any part time jobs when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No. Don't remember any home helps or anything like that them days, I don
't remember anything like that. I remember we - my mother had to pay for a doctor. Do remember that - even when - when I was married I had to - if you had the children ill you had to pay half a crown for a doctor - to come in the - doctors never got much 
m
oney in them days. They've never been so well off I don't think as they are today, because nobody ever paid 'em. They had the doctor, you had to pay when my children were born, we've had to pay for a woman to look after me, three guineas, and we had to pa
y
 three or four guineas to - for a doctor as well. But - I mean look at the benefit that they - the young people get today. Don't they? They get about twenty-four pound when they have a baby don't they, so Betty says, twenty-four pounds any rate, and then 
i
f they work - it's like me, if I'd have only - paid my stamps all the years I've been out to work, I would have got - that is only the trouble why I don't get a full pension. Because I've never paid any stamps. But you never see it at the time you know wh
a
t I mean, you don't see it 'til it's - when I - mind you I couldn't take pension until Mr Epps comes sixty-five. But I only get three pounds sixteen, I've never had the stamps. But if I'd have got me stamps like anybody else - I would have got five pound 
odd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever do any other jobs after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh I went back to work in the picture palace. My mother had - the boy while I went back to work there for a little while. And then I - had the girl, and then I went back there for a littl
e while again, so - we had a bit more extra money, but after that I packed up, I've never done no work not no more not 'til we came this way to live, and my - my little girl was three years old, then I started going out to work again, and I kept right on 
'til I was finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did you do this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
I was - doing housework. I worked for a lady over at - Royal Hospital Road for years. I was house - first in the war well I worked - I came here 1940, and I was working for - housekeeper for a - Air
 Marshall, and I was working - this other chap had got - American - he was in the - Civil Defence, not the Civil - yes, Civil Defence, both of 'em. The lady who I worked for, her husband was in the forces, but - they were very well-to-do, but he wanted to
 
go in the forces. So he joined the forces, she went in to A - ATS and left the - advertised the cottage, these people. They were friends, this Air Marshal, American and they came - together and had this - had this - took this cottage over, and I used to w
o
rk for 'em you see. Then I did this job of afternoons, in the afternoon in Hospital Road, it was in Paradise Walk, I worked there all the war. He - this - the air chap, his wife was - he's a married man, his wife was in South Africa with the little boy an
d
 they - she stopped away all the war, all while the war was on, but I never - my kids never went away, they wouldn't be evacuated, my Ronnie. They used to stop here. 'Cos my Ron went in the Army you see, had to go in the Army. Oh of course was I upset whe
n
 he had to go in the army, 'cos he was only just turned eighteen. I never thought I'd get over it, but anyhow - I did, and it done me the world of good. He was a fussy little bugger, he wouldn't eat this and he wouldn't have that and he didn't realize the
r
e was a war on and you couldn't get it, you know how we was rationed with everything that we was, I used to go round up at Gloucester Road, Alf, get a bit of fish. And he went into - Fox Photos, used to do all the - photography and all that, and he got on
 
well with it. That's why for five years they went into the glass trade, and - of course the consequence was - my sister-in-law that lives at Southend, she used to get all the food she wanted. You know that family never knew there was a war on. They used t
o get all the joints of meat, all the ham, and I mean I just - could only get here - what I could get on the books.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Going back to the time before you started work, do you ever remember whether you felt that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh well I often think they did, I don't know whether they did but I never - we never knew much you know. They never talked about it. No, not about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Your father was never ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, he was never ill or out of work, no, he wasn't, he was always working my dad was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You never had any sort of people from the Parish or the Guardians came round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh no. Don't remember anything much - only when he was taken ill, that was the only - but then we was all married, that wa
s after and - we was all married and - well provided for, all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you remember anybody in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was there anyone like that around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Well you see when we lived at Meeting House Lane a good
 many years - after you see, there - these two houses stood together, and then - along the other side was all the little shops where my mother used to shop, and you see further down as I - well we never knew many people round there sort of thing you know,
 
there wasn't many at all, just knew the shopkeepers more than you knew anybody, didn't know - people next door to me, I - I heard the other day - the mother died, he was a - fishmonger and he died then she died, and then - now I heard the other day that t
he daughter and her husband's dead so - there's all that family been wiped out, but it's funny how - just how things - you know. I suppose -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 So you didn't really know an awful lot of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, didn't know an awful - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What about at Tappersfield Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Tappersfield Road? Oh I - we had - we had my aunt living up by the side of us. That was the old - my mum used to go around with her when she bought the piano and when we was quite young there. Yes, and me granny, yes, in Turtwood R
oad, yes. That's what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You can't remember anybody who everybody sort of didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You don't remember anybody being forced to leave the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Being made to leave by rough music or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I can't remember anybody like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you remember who you thought were the most important people in the district you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I - I remember the first world war starting. When we had a German shop and everybody raided it
. And they were very nice people but all the British - people down the street, who lived in the street, they turned against 'em. They went and raided the shop. I remember me being amongst 'em and putting a couple of those - in for me mum. And me mother sa
id to me, there's no need to bring it to me, she said, we didn't need it. I said, oh well, it's all help for - they've all had a go so I thought I'd have a go too. But that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You can't remember anyone thinking anybody was particularly important in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was it very much of a community where you lived or was it sort of different people living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Well, they all sort of kept their - they were neighbourly but that's all you could say, you know, you can't say there was any di
fferent to anybody else because - they all went on the sort of same way as what my mum did you know, those that had kids. And all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 If I could ask about your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Were you ever given any lessons by your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No. We went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, mother used to take us to school. 'Til we got older, to about seven or - like that, and then she - she - sort of - you know
, left us. And come home ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What time of day did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Nine o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 When would you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 About half past four. Time you got home, 'cos we lived a decent way from the school when we lived at - at - Nun
head. But when we came to - Peckham - it was a bit nearer, the school was a bit nearer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was it the same school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. One was Park - Park Road, and the other one was - Peckham Rye. Nunhead Lane I think it was. I forget now. Can't remember
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was there much difference between the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Well, I rather liked - the Park Road one best. Was more - sports and - things you know and - more to - seemed to be more to do there.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Is that the one you went to to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, the one when I finished school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you come home to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Ay? Yes, I always came home to dinner. Always liked my dinner at home you know, never liked - used to do school dinners them days. Used to do some but - I don't know, I never liked the look of 'em.
 My mum used to have to cook for my dad 'cos he would come - always - done it - job he done he's always been a dinner hour, so he's come home so - she always cooked the dinner you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How long did it take you to get to school when you say it was quite a long walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Quite long - about twenty minutes. Mm, we used to walk there and back, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh - I didn't used to mind it, I didn't like it when I first went to school but - after I'd been there about a year or
 so I sort of got into it all like, I liked it then. But I didn't like it to start off with, not to start off with,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh, I was pretty good - I used to get on with - I think my mum had a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 rough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457  and a tumble with on
e teacher there. I can't remember - I'm just trying to think whether - what it was about you know. I know she - my mum went up the school. I think I was examined, she never knew nothing about it, I think - I think that's what it was. I was examined, she n
e
ver knew nothing about it, and - she went up there after her and said, don't - don't examine my child. I know she kicked up a hell of a stink I know, and this - governess was only a little woman and she turned round and said, oh it was only just that we p
i
cked, Lily out, we didn't have time to let you know and she said I don't care. Pickingmy daughter out she said, you just - you just let me know in the proper manner when you're going - I want to be there when you examine my daughter. And - another thing s
h
e said, you kept her in - one day she kept me in 'cos I something I done, and - she put me in the hall, and I never went home 'til about quarter to five, got home at about nearly one o'clock this day. And - so she said I've got another thing to tell you t
o
o, and she told her, there was a rough and a tumble, so anyhow - it all blew over you know, but she was funny like that, she didn't mind - being - anywhere or going anywhere if it was for us - she had our teeth out or anything like that she'd take us but 
- she didn't what upset her was over this - I think it was over examination, I don't know what it was. Medical examination you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What would happen if you had toothache and things in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh she'd buy as a - you know, a pill or somethi
ng like that you know, a - they used to call 'em Scotts, Scotts - pills were very good them days, she used to buy a packet of them and give us some of them if we had toothache.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you have dentists and things around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh dentist - there was dentists, yes, but - she used to take us sometimes to have 'em out but - I don't think I - I think I used to
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You hear terrible stories about dentists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh dentists. You know, they - when my - daughter was a little girl and she started to talk, she wa
s about seven and do you know they didn't half treat her rough. At Braniton Street up here, where they've got the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s dental, and they didn't half - and do you know after that I could never get her to a dentist any more. She wouldn't go. Her - her t
eeth was half out and they just went, and I had to take her to Doctor Brassey, a - a private doctor to have it - I had to take her 'cos it was half hanging out. They never done the job properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did your parents keep a check on what you were doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes. She always wanted to know - always used to go now and again when it was open day, you know, to see how we was getting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was that once a hear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What would happen if you did something that the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Well, they would send you in a corner or send you out in the - to the governess if you done anything wrong them days, I don't know how they go on today. With the kids I'm sure, but we - that's we always used to have to do. Go to the governess and
 get the cane. Used to cane you them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever feel that it was strict punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes. Yes, I should say so, they used to blooming hurt you any rate.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you ever get the cane yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Yes. Oh yes, I've had the cane lots of times. Never used to tell me mother though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What kind of things would you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Well - talking in class and - you know - something that I shouldn't have done or - I don't know - mostly used to be talking - I always used to chatter. Well there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was it a mixed school, girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Mixed school, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did the boys get any different punishment to the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes, they all got the cane, so we was all served alike, yes. Yes, all served alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What kind of teachers were they, were they strict people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Yes, yes, well - I don't know, they wasn't too bad but - it's all according who you had I suppose really, but some of 'em was all right. There's only one teacher I didn't like and that was a Miss P
ritchard, 'cos you used to have to in go in her club - in the other class if she was away and used to put us all together sort of - if - she was ill once, I don't know, had a - cold or something been going so - they put us in another class with a lot more
 
but I didn't like this teacher at all. I was damned glad when my teacher come back again. But - you know my mother used to take a lot of interest in us. I don't think I've ever done it what she used to do, not with my children, my - I've never worried abo
ut the school, I've just sort of let 'em get on with it, but - my mum used to go - often, if she had - felt like it, she used to go and ask the - governess, how's so and so getting on, or how's - Georgie getting on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did she ask you in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
She used to say I've been this afternoon and - to see your teacher, perhaps I wouldn't know she'd been there. And she'd say? I went to your - I was at school this afternoon. Oh get off, what did you go for mum? And she'd say, oh - what did I go for, to 
see - anyhow, good report, you're getting on all right. She'd say, I'm pleased with that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What kind of things were you good at at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Reading and things like that you know and - and - answering questions or anything like that you 
know. And - sums, I was very good at arithmetic. Adding up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being very important do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes - arithmetic - when I went to school and reading was - two of the - two - two things that
 they - I believe they used to think - 'cos we used to do such a lot of it, they - I think they used to think it was very important you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What about things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Man - oh yes, manners yes. Manners. Do you know, half the kids that lea
ve school today, they can't read or write, you know, my grandson - was fifteen before - and he couldn't read. And he couldn't write. And I never knew it, I've been down to his mother and never knew that he could - he'd been away - not up - here in London 
b
ut in here stopping here and I was down there and he was stopping with his grandad, and I - all I said to him was - was - I said, you might have sent anybody a - a postcard. So his father turned round to me, he said - he can't even write. I said, what? He
 
said, he can't read or write. I said, and you let him leave school like that? Well, since he - he got married when he was about eighteen, I said, you're mad, whatever - whatever do you want to get married for? I said, to my sister - my daughter, I said, y
ou're mad I said. So she said, oh well, what's the good, can't stand in their way, they want to do it so let 'em do it. But his wife learnt him to read. He seems to write all right now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did the teachers in the old days expect you to keep tidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh
 yes. Yes, but I'll tell you what, there was a lot of - I don't know, some people sent their kids to school, didn't care about them you know. Dirt - clothes not washed, and hair dirty. Used to get the nurse - get nurse at school a lot them days, 'cos ther
e was a lot of dirty heads about and all that with girls, but - as I say - that's another thing in the past now you don't see nothing like that in the schools today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Were they from the same kind of home as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I think they came from a poorer home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did they have any favourites or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Yes, oh yes, I'll tell you - these - some of these kids, you know, you know, we - I 
think didn't hardly used to have enough to eat, but - the extra milk, you see teachers give it to these children you know, you know, that was - and things that - they'd bring in shopping and here's a - a bit of cake left you see and go and give to the kid
s
 you know - I suppose - as I say, they was very rough times them times, and I mean I suppose somebody had to look after these people but - whether the - parents - whatever happened why I don't know. We never heard it talked about much but there was this m
i
lk going or - as I say this teacher that we had used to bring in a bag of cakes and - I think there's a couple she'd bring 'em back wherever she went to lunch she'd bring 'em back and we see her - pass 'em to this children you know, perhaps a - you know, 
looked hungry., they really did, some of them did look hungry. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Were there any gangs in the school or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. I never ever remembered any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you remember any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh no, I mean - this teacher we had - I - no, I think they were all - you know, they looked after all of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 It was a - what they call a - used to call it - just LCC school. A Board school. Board school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, was a Board 
school. No, wasn't a church school. My mother didn't believe my mother didn't believe in - she wanted a proper school. When we had to go to another school she raked round 'til she found the right thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did she object to in a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
I don't know why she objected and yet my children went there. But - I don't know what she objected to. Don't know what the objection was at all, but she said she didn't like it, didn't like church - she - I don't know, it's like they've always said in thi
s - later years, you know, when my children - went to a - church school and then they went to the board school when we moved out, they - they don't like it you know. They don't reckon - I don't know what it is, I think they - think they learn too much rel
igion and don't learn the - the basic things. But kids should learn. Which I think is very important really. I think reading and writing - for a child is very important today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 So you think you benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 ed a lot from your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you go on to any other school after you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I didn't go - no - only went to two schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Have you got any regrets about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, no, I don't think so. I'll tell you what, I - as I'm getting older 
now I - I - I write a letter and I sort of get - sometimes cross with a word, you know what I mean? And I can't - and I say to my husband, how do you spell so and so? And perhaps it's quite easy. But that's to think of it, I cannot spell it. And I say to 
him, what's so and so - well, that's spelt - oh - oh yes, that's right, so it is. But for the life of me I can't spell it - I can't spell it when I'm writing. Isn't it funny? Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Fourteen. But mind you I was at school all the time, my mother kept me there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Would you have stayed on any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Yes, I believe I would have done. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No, I never went, no. Onl
y one - only one of my family did and my family and that was my boy, he went and learnt all about - motors and things like that. But he - he - he's the what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 name - he - he wasn't very good at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you remember whether you'd got your job fixed up before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
No, we - mother went to school and asked what we was going to do, and 'course I kept on about being a nurse. And I was - always got it in my brain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 box I wanted to be a nurse, I don't know why, but of course - they said that
 I'd have to train, and that - cost money them days. And I suppose - it meant a lot to parents them days, money you know, wasn't as if I was an only child, I was one of four - seven of us, so of course I never got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Would your father be in the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Ay? Was, yes, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 So he wouldn't be there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. But - no, I didn't - I didn't know it at all, I didn't have that job at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Who got the job in Petticoat Lane for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh I went after it meself, I saw it 
advertised and I went after it meself. Yes, me and my - me and my sister went after it. In the finish I got my sister there and - my brother got there and I got his wife there and - three of us together in the finish there. Well I wasn't there very long.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Can you ever remember any kind of apprenticeship or training scheme for these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 I don't know, I - I think my brother went in for something like that. Can't remember. Not me, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Were you ever a member of any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, I can't remember any trades union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you get on all right with your employers, did you feel that they had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Five shilling increase.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Rise, yes. It was a lot of money, I know - only for - it was only about six of us worked ther
e, wasn't many - two or three men, wasn't many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
In these jobs that you worked in did you ever notice any division of interest amongst the workers themselves? Was there any distinction between a craftsman I don't suppose you'd notice it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No. No I wouldn't - no, I never noticed anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you think that fulltime work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh - I don't know - I mean most of it was full time wasn't it, from eight o'clock 'til - half past five 
as much as they do now really. Some - some were six o'clock, but they never got holidays with pay like they've got now, nothing like that. That was right out the question. Even when my husband was working when he was working on a - right out what}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 name I 
mean he - where was it - Warwickshire, no not Warwickshire - right out somewhere I know - Dulwich way I think it was, he was doing all these - these things - what are they - telephone things you know on the - pulling all the - the tops up you know and thi
ngs and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457  cementing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 all round, them days I mean to say if they - if it poured with rain they never got the wages. No, there's no - no - not much money coming in them days, which is a good thing you know with wages and - pay.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Where did you first meet your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
In the picture palace. He came to work there after I'd been there a long time. And they said to me - somebody to me - we've got a new chap starting in the stalls. I said, oh yes? So I was up in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457  what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 name and - they said - a girl 
came up to me and they said oh this is George.. I said, yes there was one girl who was very sweet on him. I wonder she never ever got him to tell you the truth, but - I said, oh yes, so - then a little while after - he said to me, what day do you have off
?
 I said, - I used to always have Thursdays, and he said, would you like to come to the pictures and we sort of did and we went out together - for about eighteen months. And - mm, and then I - he said to me one day, he said, I haven't got much life at home
, he said, my mum's out - to work all the time, he said, and - he was - but he was last one at home, all the others were married you see, and he said, there's only me and my dad at home, my dad does shift work in the gas company -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 How far away did he live from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
In Brixton. Up - up by the White Horse. Not - oh - 'cos a decent way from Peckham any way. And - he said - and he popped the question. And of course I thought to myself, well I might as well - get married, have a home of me own, I rathe
r liked the idea of it so - we got - well, I went with him about a twelve month, I was engaged about six months, that was all. And then we were married like in the - Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you go down to his home very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Yes, I went home but th
ere was never nobody there - His sister used to keep house for his mother while his mother used to go to work, and she had a family and I used to go up there quite a lot and see the kids you know and see my sister-in-law..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was it an arranged meeting the first time you went round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Oh yes, arranged yes. Yes, his mother - all his mother - I think he's a bit a devil at home, between me and you, well I know so now but I didn't know then because I had to meet his mother and father, and - I was su
pposed to go to dinner this day, and - oh she said - he said, oh, he said, we're engaged. He said, I've brought Lily up to show you mum to show you her ring. He buy - bought me half hoop diamond so his mother said - just looked at me, not very - nicely yo
u
 know, and she said, look here George, she said - a wife expects a week's money. Not once now and again, every week. And she said, you'll have to learn to do it, she said, that's the only thing - so all I put it down to after was I don't think he ever giv
e
 up much money at home. 'Cos I said to him after do you pay up at home? I said, yes, she ain't like my mother, my mother - even when I said to my mum when I was getting married I said - could I give you so much less mum? And she said, no you damned well c
a
n't, you want to get married, she said, I want my wages off of you right up to the time you're married. And what I buy you I buy you, but she was very decent but she wouldn't lower the wages. But I don't think my George give up much money at home because 
- she was very offhanded. I know I kicked his foot under the table. And I said when she turned her back, let's hurry up and go. And - I - she said -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did you go round very often after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 I - I - afterwards I - now and again I went round and - 
and I said to her one day after we'd been married about two years, I said to her about - talking one day and I said, always remember mother what you said. And she said, well, he did, he was a devil. He never gave up any money, he - used to want his food a
n
d he didn't care a damn, she said, I - if I had any wages or not. All because I used to go myself. So she said, it was just a word of warning, and she said, how you getting on my girl, she said, is he bad? Oh I said, I don't have no trouble with the wages
. She said, well I'm very glad, I didn't - that's what she said to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did his father do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 His father was in the gas company too. He used to take big money, his fath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 
er was a - old ti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 er in the gas company you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did he do in the gas company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Stoking. We - it was hard work them days, you see that's all machinery today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Was your husband brought up to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh no, nothing of that. Well - I don't think - I think they just let him get on his own - t
he difference in families, I think they just left him to get on with his - his brother - his father always used to be on shift work and his mother used to work as a cook in Alexandra - Palace and she was always at work you never ever catch - if you caught
 her when you went up there -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Alexandra Palace in North London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
Yes. And that's where she used to work there, and - she was a cook there. She learnt me - she learnt me how to cook when I first married. My - I - I - one day I was cooking a Yorksh
ire pudding and my nephew came down the stairs, 'cos he used to live there with his father, it was a great big house, him and his - her other son used to live on the middle flo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457  and I was coming - down the stairs with this Yorkshire pudding. And he laughe
d at me. And I said - how dare you laugh at me Jack, I said, who do you think you are. So he said, some better pudding, he said, Uncle George eat that? So - I said, yes, he does, he's at - he's ate it all these years, I said, he's not dead yet, and laughe
d
, you know. And - 'course his mother, she's very very - she's a lovely woman, she said to me afterwards - don't take no notice of Jack - of Jack - Lilly, he said, he's only pulling your leg. I said, yes, I know, but I can tell him. But anyhow - she said t
o me this Sunday, she said, bring your flour down here and your eggs and that, she said, I'll show you how to do a bit of cooking. I said, well my mum wasn't much of a cook. And - she learnt me to cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 So you go on very well with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 I got very well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did you call his parents before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
I used to call her Mrs Gammon. That's what her name was - because she'd been married twice you see. Her - my husband's - father - he was a riding master, and he was kicked by a ho
rse, and then she married again and all the children that she'd had - she'd had a family, was by the first husband, and they didn't have no children with this - 'cos she must have been getting on when she married this other one, and you know this chap tha
t was - he was a great big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 man, we used to call him - oh it's - no, I never used to call him dad - Joe I think his name was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What did you call them after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Ay? Oh - I used to say dad and mum, mm. And - and do you know he came down with my
 - he - he never was ill, and he came down this night, he was going on night work, on a Sunday night, she'd just made a cup of tea and she had - some of the grandchildren, as well, and he just bent down \{BLANK\}
 took nine policeman to carry him up the top of the house. Great big fellow. Oh he was a great big fellow. But very nice, they were both very very good to me, they really were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 You'd often go round there after you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes. Mm. And - and my - yes, oh yes, I used to go and - help her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5788053\charrsid1641457  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
sometimes you know. Do a bit of ironing or something like that or much about. And she loved the kids. You know my kids got up in the morning and I used to have to go top of the house to the bottom for - water. And - do you know that - they both get d
own there, she's say, hello my loves, to 'em both you know. I used to have one on me - 'cos there's only about two and a half years between the boy and the girl, and she'd say - hello my loves, I'm going to have me breakfast now, granny - granny - she alw
a
ys used to say, granny's going to have her breakfast. She'd tuck into - eggs and bacon, well before I knew what I was saying she'd be cooking them eggs and bacon, getting their chairs out, I said oh mother but they've had their breakfast. You can eat a bi
t
 more can't you, she'd say to 'em, and they'd both sit there - and have eggs and bacon for their breakfast. Ah she's a dear really she was. I - she was - everybody loved her down where they - where we lived you know. More so I can remember her more so tha
n
 - well they used to run after her if there was any trouble, and I've seen her - an old tramp on a Sunday with - perhaps going - a bloke going down the street singing. You know she's gone up and brought him in to a great big dinner. I said to her, mother 
y
ou can't do that. Oh poor man, he needs it. See, and perhaps take all she's got in her purse and give to him. That's the sort of woman she was. And when my husband was out of work - up there, she - every weekend, mum, I don't want you to give it to me. Sh
e had it all but she never used to give it to - she wouldn't help you out. She thought that you'd married, you get on with it. But not his mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Did the two sets of parents meet each other before the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh yes, they - they come and - but - I
 don't think she liked my mum and I don't think my mum liked her much. But she was ever so kind to me though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 What about the two sets of dads, did they get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh they got on all right, but the mums didn't get on very well, but - she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Do you remember the first time that he came back to your place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Oh he came - who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Your husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 
No, my mother thought the world of my husband, so did my father. Right 'til he died, he always said that - my George would look after her - her
 - my mother when he died which he did. But - oh I don't know, but - the old lady she didn't like my - my mother, I think she thought she was a bit too hard on the family you know. Because she wasn't hard sort of woman, everybody loved her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 Before you started courting did his parents know your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 No, not before we sort of - you know, got together properly, when I got engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11756613 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 When did they first meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6241478 LE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736647\charrsid1641457 They came down to see us after we got engaged.
\par }}